{"questionId":"14619858","questionHtml":"<p>Given that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math>, find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>Noting that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to differentiate numerator and denominator:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(evaluates to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn></mfrac></math>) and attempts to differentiate a second time:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award relevant marks, even if '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder></math>'is not explicitly seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to express&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;as a Maclaurin series&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mtext>terms&nbsp;in</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This <em><strong>R1</strong></em> is awarded independently of any other marks.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Award relevant marks, even if '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder></math>'is not explicitly seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>splitting function into<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;and using limit of product = product of limits&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>×</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>using L’ Hôpitals rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>using Maclaurin expansion for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mtext>terms</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>in</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>hence<em><strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>⇒</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong></em>Award relevant marks, even if '<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder></math>'is not explicitly seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"14619858","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ1.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that limx→0fx=16, find the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}